<h1><span id="French_Defence:_Advance_Variation">French Defence: Advance Variation</span></h1>
<p>Here, after White's 4. c3, Black usually decides to increase the pressure on White's center pawns (d4/e5) by playing 4...Nc6. <br>
Another plausible plan for Black is 4...Qb6, which also increases the pressure on d4, and allows the manoeuver 5...Bd7 followed by 6...Bb5. The idea is to trade Black's 'bad' bishop for White's 'good' bishop.
</p>
<p><b>1.e4 e6 2.d4 d5 3.e5 c5 4.c3</b>
</p>
